2017 WW11 Purley Crystal Ridge BKC Release Announcement (BKC #2)

\n \n \n

DEG Platform Integration Team

\n \n
\n

The DEG platform Integration team announces the release of 2017 WW11 Purley Crystal Ridge BKC release package for Intel internal use. The release is based on OS of\n \n Fedora24\n server. The auto-installer packages are available in the Artifactory server (both SH site and OR site). Any questions please contact Bei, Ling.

Test Result:

\xc2\xb7       \nFinish\nAEP test execution on Fedora24 (kernel is upgraded to 4.9.13 ) on 2-2-2\nconfig (1LM + AppDirect). Please visit HPQC for test\ndetail

\xc2\xb7       \nRefer\nto the installation guide BKC package installation

\n\n\n\n

\xc2\xb7       \nTotal\ntest case: 21; Passed test case is: 15 and pass rate is 72%

 

Mandatory\nBIOS settings:

\xc2\xb7       EDKII menu -> Socket Configuration -> Memory\nConfiguration-> Attempt Fast Boot\n<disable>

\xc2\xb7       EDKII menu -> Socket Configuration -> Memory\nConfiguration-> Attempt Fast Boot Attempt Fast Cold Boot <disable>

\xc2\xb7       EDKII menu -> Socket\nConfiguration -> Advanced Power Management\nConfiguration -> Package C State\nControl/Package C State < C0/C1 state>

\xc2\xb7       EDKII menu -> Socket\nConfiguration -> UPI Configuration ->\nUPI General Configuration -> Directory Mode Enable <Disable>

\xc2\xb7       EDKII menu -> Socket\nConfiguration -> Memory Configuration ->\nMemory Frequency <2400>

 

ES1 AEP DIMM Setup BKM 

\xc2\xb7       \nUpdate CR FW

If AEP DIMM is not healthy, use ITP/Jtag to update AEP FW and Syn\nSPD one by one, follow the BKM Setup_TAB_AEP_BKM_v1.1.docx

If AEP DIMM is health, use either ITP/Jtag or UEFI shell to\nupdate all AEP FW

              \nApachePassCli.efi\nload \xe2\x80\x93f -source <path_to_strip.bin> - dimm\n

 

\xc2\xb7     Goal/namespace can be\ncreated under UEFI or Linux

a.     \n    UEFI:\nApachePassCli.efi create -f -goal PersistentMemoryType=AppDirect

          \n      ApachePassCli.efi\nshow -a \xe2\x80\x93pool

         \n       ApachePassCli.efi\ncreate \xe2\x80\x93namespace \xe2\x80\x93pool <pool_Id> Type=AppDirect

b.          Linux: ixpdimm-cli create\n\xe2\x80\x93f \xe2\x80\x93goal persistentmemorytype=appdirect

           \n       ixpdimm-\ncli show -a \xe2\x80\x93pool

\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n                   ixpdimm-cli create \xe2\x80\x93namespace \xe2\x80\x93pool\n<pool_Id> Type=AppDirect

Pedigree and Board Jumper Settings: 2S Guide

Note: Only mandatory and necessary optional rework is implemented by BKC team

\xc2\xb7      2s

o NC_RWK_I (Mandatory): Update BMC FW

o NC_RWK_K (Mandatory): Avoiding false LAN Wake Activations

o NC_RWK_L (Mandatory): Update CPLD FW

o NC_RWK_M (Mandatory): No-Boot without ITP issue fix

o Note: In case you have implemented Optional rework 20, you should move switch S4E2.4 to OFF position, otherwise the default position is ON.
